<br>
You have to kill the runners until &quot;A Brigand&quot; spawns in the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> right</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> place. <br>
<br>
&quot;A Brigand&quot; won't despawn and respawn as Vilnus if it's in spawned in the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> wrong</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> location.<br>
<br>
if &quot;A Brigand&quot; spawns in the wrong place then you have to kill that one and keep killing the runners until you get him in the right place.<br>
<br>
I found this out the hard way... The person selling me the Kedge MQ was not impressed that I could not spawn the guy and they had to come back the next day.<br>
<br>
The Matt Waggoner guide had this part wrong (otherwise it was superb).<br>
The Safehouse guide has it right I believe.<br>
<br>
So go read that guide <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
<br>
p.s. Only kill &quot;a Brigand&quot; if he pops in the wrong place (i.e. down in the camp with the other guys.). Otherwise he must be kept alive til he depops. <br>
